PROJECT REPORT

Title: Money Management Software (Tkinter)


---

1. Introduction

This project is a desktop-based money management system built using Python and Tkinter.
The software helps users record daily expenses and incomes, set a monthly budget, view financial summaries, and monitor whether they are within their spending limits.

It provides a clean graphical interface and simple workflows suitable for personal finance tracking.


---

2. Objectives

The main objectives of the application are:

To provide a simple GUI for recording expenses and incomes.

To allow users to set and adjust their monthly budget.

To summarize expenses, incomes, and remaining balance.

To store and show transactions in an organized format.

To notify the user when they exceed the budget.



---

3. Features

3.1 Add Expense

Users can record an expense by entering:

Amount

Date (Day, Month, Year)

Note/description


The valid entry gets added to the internal list.

3.2 Add Income

Similar to expenses, this records:

Amount

Date

Note


3.3 Delete Last Entry

If user selects Yes, the last expense is deleted.

If user selects No, the last income is deleted.


3.4 Show Expenses

Displays:

All saved expenses

Date, Amount, Note

Total expenses at bottom


3.5 Show Incomes

Displays:

All saved incomes

Total income


3.6 Set Budget

Allows the user to change the monthly budget. The interface automatically updates the displayed budget.

3.7 Check Expenses (Budget Check)

Displays:

Total expenses

Remaining budget

Warning message if the user overspends


3.8 Show All Transactions

Shows incomes and expenses together, along with:

Total income

Total expenses

Net balance


3.9 Exit Application

Prompts for confirmation before closing the window.


---

4. System Requirements

Software

Python 3.10

Tkinter (bundled with Python)


Hardware

Any modern system with basic processing power

Minimum screen resolution 800Ã—600



---

5. Technologies Used

Component	Technology

GUI	Tkinter
Date Handling	datetime
Dialogs	simpledialog, messagebox
Data Storage	Python lists (in-memory)



---

6. Code Structure

Classes

1. BudgetManager

Handles:

GUI layout

Storing expenses/incomes

Displaying summaries

Budget logic

Main application control


2. EntryDialog

Handles:

Expense/Income input form

Validations

Returning results to main class


Main

Creates the Tk root and runs the GUI loop.


